{
  "texts": [
    "HGAT comprises a two-level attention mechanism for both node-level attention and schema-level attention.",
    "The node-level attention mechanism learns the weights of neighbors belonging to the same type and aggregates them to derive the type-specific neighbor representation.",
    "The schema-level attention allows the HGAT model to capture the information regarding node types and achieve an optimally weighted combination of type-specific neighbor representations.",
    "HGAT is employed in two major components: HGAT-based classifier and HGAT-based selector.",
    "The HGAT-based classifier utilizes both labeled and unlabeled data to predict labels for unlabeled news article nodes."
  ]
}